      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Generating the die images for the bonding diagrams was quite easy, I simply edited the reticle stitcher script.\nYou can find the images for all public designs here: https://drive.proton.me/urls/SFX6Q4D4RR#LFPgOT92assa\nI enabled the top two metal layers and set the pad layer to a solid color.\n\nJust by quickly looking through the images, I found a number of designs that didn't adhere to the default padring: 2975, OCD1, AF01\nI hope those designs have selected bare dies for packaging. (@Tim 'mithro' Ansell)\n\n@Andrew Wingate If you'd like to use these images for the bonding diagrams, let me know, and I can send you the full, unobfuscated set. I can also add metadata, e.g., the slot size, to the image names if that helps.\nIn this run, the QR code is at the bottom left of all designs. However, that is just by coincidence, as it was not a requirement for the customer.",
